#3.1How does the tipping amount (tip) depend on the overall bill (total_bill)? 
ggplot(tips,aes(x=total_bill,y=tip))+ geom_point()

cor(tips$tip, tips$total_bill)
## [1] 0.6757341
#3.2describe the relationship in words. 
#The points have a linear, and positive moderate association. 
#As total_bill increases, tips also tends to increase. 
#There are series outliers in both x and y.

#3.3 Describe at least two types of anomalies in the plot. What do they mean?

#5 How does smoking behavior and gender of the person who pays 
#impact the relationship between tip and total bill? 

ggplot(tips,aes(x=total_bill,y=tip))+geom_point()+facet_grid(.~smoker+sex)

#The plot of the non-smoker are stronger than the plot of the somkers. It means that the smokers are more casual about the tips.
#Gender doesnt impact the realtionship too much,just there are more men pay more bill with high tips.

#6.Use ggplot2 to find a graphical summary of the relationship between 
#day of the week and gender of the person paying the bill. 

ggplot(tips,aes(x=day,fill=total_bill))+geom_bar(position="stack")+facet_grid(.~sex)

# There is no obvious difference between the bill female and male pay on Friday and Thursday.
# But on the Saturday, the male pay the bill double as the female. On the Sunday,the male pay the bill triple as the female
#It possibily means the male are more generous during the weekend
